com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.models

Class GroupedCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.models.GroupedCollection
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImmutableGroupedCollection

    public abstract class GroupedCollection
extends java.lang.Object
    Collection of several groups of series. Each group is a list of series, and the group is identified by its series key. Internally groups are stored as a Map: SeriesKey -> List of Series.
    All statistics/aggregation functions are calculated for each group in turn. Method naming convention:
    1. Method named as some statistical/aggregation function, e.g. sum(), median() etc., do calculations for each timestamp. So the function is calculated for the set of values with given timestamp from different series of the same group.
    2. Methods with prefix "total" apply aggregation function to set of values with different timestamps and from all series of the same group. These methods generate either single scalar or single regular series for each group.
